  level: Level 19
  name: Center of Mass and Momentum
  description: Center of mass the balance point of an object and momentum, showing
    how mass and velocity affect motion and impact.
  quizItems:
  - rid: 138986247837974657
  - rid: 138986247837974658
  - rid: 138986247837974659
  - rid: 138986247837974660
  - rid: 138986247837974661
  - rid: 138986247837974662
  - rid: 138986247837974663
  - rid: 138986247837974664
  references:
    version: 2
    RefIds:
    - rid: 138986247837974657
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - What is the center of mass in an object? Which of the following best describes
          this?
        - Which best defines the center of mass? Which of the following is correct?
        - Which statement best describes the center of mass? Which of the following
          is correct?
        correctAnswer:
        - The balance point or average position of mass
        wrongAnswers:
        - The heaviest part of the body
        - The outermost edge of the object
        - The point farthest from the axis
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 138986247837974658
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - Momentum is described as? Which of the following best defines it?
        - Which statement best explains momentum? Which of the following is correct?
        - Which of the followig is the correct meaning of momentum?
        correctAnswer:
        - Mass multiplied by velocity
        wrongAnswers:
        - Distance over time
        - Weight of an object
        - Energy in rotation
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 138986247837974659
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - The correct SI unit of momentum is? Which of the following is correct?
        - What unit is used to measure momentum? Which of the following is correct?
        - Which of the following is the SI unit for momentum?
        correctAnswer:
        - "Kilogram-meter per second (kg\xB7m/s)"
        wrongAnswers:
        - Newton (N)
        - Joule (J)
        - Watt (W)
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 138986247837974660
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - The formula for the center of mass of two objects is? Which of the following
          is correct?
        - Which of these shows how to compute the center of mass (COM) for two objects?
          Which of the following is correct?
        - Which equation is used to find the center of mass (COM) of two objects?
          Which of the following is correct?
        correctAnswer:
        - (m1 * x1 + m2 * x2) / (m1 + m2)
        wrongAnswers:
        - (m1 + m2) / (x1 + x2)
        - m1 x1 m2 x2
        - (x1 + x2) / (m1 * m2)
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 138986247837974661
      type: {class: SolvingItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 1
        question:
        - A ball of mass {m1} kg is at position {x1} meters, and a box of mass {m2}
          kg is at position {x2} meters along a straight line. Find the center of
          mass of these two objects.
        formula: (m1 * x1 + m2 * x2) / (m1 + m2)
        variables:
        - variable: m1
          name: Mass 1
          unit: kg
          range:
            min: 2
            max: 2
        - variable: x1
          name: Position 1
          unit: m
          range:
            min: 1
            max: 1
        - variable: m2
          name: Mass 2
          unit: kg
          range:
            min: 4
            max: 4
        - variable: x2
          name: Position 2
          unit: m
          range:
            min: 5
            max: 5
        variable: COM
        name: Center of Mass
        unit: m
        rounding: 2
    - rid: 138986247837974662
      type: {class: SolvingItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - A ball with a mass of {m} kg moves with a velocity of {v} m/s. Find its
